New Records: Oklahoma City Thunder improved on the best start in team history by moving to 7-0 this season.
Key Match Events: Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Orlando Magic 102-86.
Jalen Williams scored 19 points in the first half.
Isaiah Joe made three 3-pointers during a 13-1 run to close the third quarter.
Chet Holmgren had nine rebounds and a couple of blocks.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Thunder's defense has been stifling all season, allowing only 86 points against Orlando.
The Thunder are on their first seven-game winning streak since 2019.
